1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:00:01,330 --> 00:00:06,890
You don't want us to open the country either.

3
00:00:06,890 --> 00:00:08,530
Right?

4
00:00:09,980 --> 00:00:15,860
Because in order to fight pirates,
you buy weapons from pirates.

5
00:00:18,160 --> 00:00:21,220
Don't you find it strange?

6
00:00:21,220 --> 00:00:22,930
Hmm?!

7
00:00:26,890 --> 00:00:31,460
With your broker Doflamingo,
also known as Joker, out of the picture,

8
00:00:31,460 --> 00:00:39,180
you have no choice but
to trade with us directly.

9
00:00:39,180 --> 00:00:45,520
I know you're out on a limb,
so the advantage is mine...

10
00:00:47,390 --> 00:00:50,820
And already your demands are unreasonable.

11
00:00:50,820 --> 00:00:55,780
Look, Wano is entirely self-sufficient!

12
00:01:01,410 --> 00:01:05,540
Everyone here seems happy, right?

13
00:01:05,540 --> 00:01:10,170
If there is something we need,
that would be greater power!

14
00:01:10,170 --> 00:01:13,590
This time, I'm only asking for a warship...

15
00:01:14,970 --> 00:01:19,180
Next time, I'll want Dr. Vegapunk!

16
00:01:19,180 --> 00:01:21,010
That's impossible!

17
00:01:26,140 --> 00:01:29,730
I didn't ask if it's possible!

18
00:01:34,030 --> 00:01:37,590
The Celestial Dragons? The Marines?

19
00:01:37,590 --> 00:01:42,410
You know we're not afraid of them, right?

20
00:01:46,080 --> 00:01:50,290
You couldn't bring us down
even if you all banded together.

21
00:01:50,290 --> 00:01:54,840
I have Kaido backing me after all!

22
00:03:49,170 --> 00:03:55,630
Oiran Komurasaki Arrives

23
00:04:00,590 --> 00:04:05,390
Komurasaki the top oiran is in procession!

24
00:04:05,390 --> 00:04:08,420
Oh, Lady Komuraski!

25
00:04:08,420 --> 00:04:11,480
Look over here, Oiran!

26
00:04:18,210 --> 00:04:20,280
I'm sorry I'm late!

27
00:04:24,070 --> 00:04:26,120
I was worried about you.

28
00:04:27,490 --> 00:04:29,790
Please forgive me, Big Sis!

29
00:04:29,790 --> 00:04:31,930
Now, get to work.

30
00:04:32,650 --> 00:04:33,870
Okay!

31
00:04:39,590 --> 00:04:42,380
Here comes Lady Komurasaki!

32
00:04:45,180 --> 00:04:47,350
It's the oiran's procession!

33
00:04:48,690 --> 00:04:49,760
Isn't she here yet?!

34
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:52,860
There're tons of people here.

35
00:04:52,860 --> 00:04:56,400
I wonder how beautiful she is!

36
00:04:56,400 --> 00:05:00,150
Please hurry, Komurasaki my beloved!

37
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:09,080
That conniving tramp...

38
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:11,160
...Komurasaki!

39
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:12,580
Komurasaki!

40
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:15,410
Komurasaki...!

41
00:05:17,460 --> 00:05:19,840
I think they're looking for trouble!

42
00:05:21,010 --> 00:05:22,370
H-Hey!

43
00:05:22,370 --> 00:05:23,840
I've got to...

44
00:05:23,840 --> 00:05:25,880
kill that bitch!

45
00:05:26,470 --> 00:05:29,260
I'll be driven out of the city...

46
00:05:29,270 --> 00:05:31,470
It's all over!

47
00:05:31,470 --> 00:05:34,220
If I'm gonna die,

48
00:05:34,220 --> 00:05:36,440
I'll take her with me!

49
00:05:46,350 --> 00:05:48,660
Stay away from the oiran!

50
00:06:01,670 --> 00:06:04,620
Komurasaki...

51
00:06:08,900 --> 00:06:13,560
I want to be with you forever, my love...

52
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:14,450
What?

53
00:06:14,980 --> 00:06:17,890
W-With an old geezer like me?!

54
00:06:17,890 --> 00:06:22,580
If I have to live Shogun Orochi's puppet...

55
00:06:22,580 --> 00:06:26,860
I would rather you bought out my contract...

56
00:06:26,860 --> 00:06:30,910
Alas, the price for my freedom is so outrageous,

57
00:06:30,910 --> 00:06:33,870
it is an impossible dream...

58
00:06:33,870 --> 00:06:39,110
Imagine if Shogun Orochi were
to catch wind of this conversation.

59
00:06:40,010 --> 00:06:42,000
Don't fret, my dear!

60
00:06:42,740 --> 00:06:44,750
If that is your desire,

61
00:06:44,750 --> 00:06:48,550
I, Bingo, will make it happen!

62
00:06:50,700 --> 00:06:52,800
Really?

63
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:56,980
I'm glad to hear it, even if you're not serious.

64
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:02,990
You don't have enough money
to pay me back?!

65
00:07:02,990 --> 00:07:04,470
I'm sorry!

66
00:07:04,470 --> 00:07:07,110
Do you take me for a fool?!

67
00:07:07,780 --> 00:07:10,750
You think crying will help?!

68
00:07:10,750 --> 00:07:14,600
I'll take your house as collateral for the loan!

69
00:07:16,870 --> 00:07:19,210
Here, Komurasaki.

70
00:07:19,210 --> 00:07:22,900
I've never seen so much money!

71
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:28,410
Komurasaki, here's an advance
to buy you from the pleasure hall.

72
00:07:28,410 --> 00:07:31,290
It's not enough yet,
but I want you to hold onto it.

73
00:07:31,290 --> 00:07:33,700
Then, let me enter it in the ledger.

74
00:07:33,700 --> 00:07:35,640
That's not necessary!

75
00:07:35,640 --> 00:07:39,350
Only a fool mistrusts the woman he loves.

76
00:07:39,350 --> 00:07:41,890
Your word is good enough for me.

77
00:07:41,890 --> 00:07:43,620
My lord Bingo...

78
00:07:44,690 --> 00:07:49,320
I cannot wait for the moment
you take me with you.

79
00:07:55,700 --> 00:07:57,900
Don't cry.

80
00:07:58,770 --> 00:07:59,750
It's all right!

81
00:07:59,750 --> 00:08:02,640
I'll make the funeral arrangements.

82
00:08:02,640 --> 00:08:06,220
I'll also lend you some money
for it and for living expenses.

83
00:08:09,210 --> 00:08:11,970
Stop crying already!

84
00:08:11,970 --> 00:08:14,940
You need to pay me back double!

85
00:08:14,940 --> 00:08:18,550
It's your own fault for being so naive!

86
00:08:20,840 --> 00:08:22,770
Here's your money!

87
00:08:22,770 --> 00:08:25,160
Wow! It's so much!

88
00:08:26,210 --> 00:08:27,400
But...

89
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:29,090
What's wrong?

90
00:08:29,090 --> 00:08:34,430
The truth is, someone else recently
offered to buy my contract...

91
00:08:34,430 --> 00:08:35,660
What?!

92
00:08:35,660 --> 00:08:37,030
I have to hurry!

93
00:08:37,030 --> 00:08:42,040
I need more and more money to buy her...
Is there anything that I can sell?

94
00:08:44,210 --> 00:08:47,420
I sold my storehouse, Komurasaki!

95
00:08:47,420 --> 00:08:50,590
I'm so grateful...

96
00:08:50,590 --> 00:08:52,590
Enough is enough!

97
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:56,170
I'm fed up with you!

98
00:08:56,930 --> 00:09:00,000
I'm going back to my parents' house!

99
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:02,060
Do whatever you like!

100
00:09:04,290 --> 00:09:08,060
I'm on my way, Komurasaki!

101
00:09:10,560 --> 00:09:12,460
I've even abandoned my family!

102
00:09:14,610 --> 00:09:18,360
Oh no, you must think of your health...

103
00:09:19,300 --> 00:09:21,910
Medicine is a waste of money.

104
00:09:21,910 --> 00:09:24,010
I'll be fine.

105
00:09:24,010 --> 00:09:31,130
Once I get what I want,
I'll be the happiest man in the world.

106
00:09:31,130 --> 00:09:38,340
I admit that I dream of my life
with you every single night...

107
00:09:38,340 --> 00:09:42,190
Oh... Komurasaki!

108
00:09:47,310 --> 00:09:48,860
I got the last of it...

109
00:09:48,860 --> 00:09:54,240
I may not have a house, but we'll be
free to start our new life together!

110
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:57,240
I have the final 500 gold.

111
00:09:57,240 --> 00:10:02,240
With this, I can buy your
contract, Komurasaki!

112
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:05,450
Huh?

113
00:10:05,450 --> 00:10:09,630
I'm sorry. The oiran is sick today...

114
00:10:09,630 --> 00:10:11,340
Oh no!

115
00:10:12,070 --> 00:10:16,460
Just be sure to give her this. I'll be back later...

116
00:10:22,280 --> 00:10:24,560
Komurasaki!

117
00:10:24,560 --> 00:10:31,430
I've come to liberate you from
the pleasure hall! Come live with me!

118
00:10:42,990 --> 00:10:45,460
You really fell for it!

119
00:10:45,460 --> 00:10:48,620
Way to go, you old pervert!

120
00:10:49,610 --> 00:10:52,210
Hey, guys!

121
00:10:52,210 --> 00:10:56,810
Quit laughing and get Komurasaki for me.

122
00:10:58,900 --> 00:11:03,100
She's going to live happily ever after with me!

123
00:11:05,600 --> 00:11:08,940
You moron! Dream on!

124
00:11:08,940 --> 00:11:11,100
You have enough money to liberate her?

125
00:11:11,100 --> 00:11:15,730
Of course I do! Komurasaki already has it!
I asked her to keep it safe for me!

126
00:11:17,700 --> 00:11:20,150
Oh my... It's Mr. Bingo.

127
00:11:20,150 --> 00:11:24,670
Oh, Komurasaki! Please set things straight!

128
00:11:24,670 --> 00:11:30,240
They're running their mouths, completely
unaware of our devotion to one another!

129
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:31,600
Oh?

130
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:37,670
You gave me that money, did you not?

131
00:11:38,390 --> 00:11:39,220
What?!

132
00:11:45,830 --> 00:11:48,970
I've already spent it all.

133
00:11:50,010 --> 00:11:51,560
But thank you.

134
00:11:53,790 --> 00:11:59,320
This old coot really thought
Komurasaki was in love with him!

135
00:12:12,700 --> 00:12:15,880
What's with the old fart?

136
00:12:15,880 --> 00:12:16,710
What?

137
00:12:16,710 --> 00:12:18,670
Komurasaki...

138
00:12:20,670 --> 00:12:23,340
B-Boss Kyoshiro!

139
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:25,720
So...

140
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:30,850
you're the old man who's been hanging
around Komurasaki these days...

141
00:12:30,850 --> 00:12:34,400
Hanging around...? L-Let me explain!

142
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:37,980
Komurasaki, this is a joke, right?

143
00:12:40,570 --> 00:12:44,500
I really did sacrifice all I had!

144
00:12:44,500 --> 00:12:46,740
I don't have anything left!

145
00:12:46,740 --> 00:12:50,660
I gave it all up for you!

146
00:13:01,100 --> 00:13:02,920
Well then...

147
00:13:02,920 --> 00:13:05,210
How many of these saps has it been now?

148
00:13:05,210 --> 00:13:09,500
We can't have you crying out here
and obstructing business, old man.

149
00:13:09,500 --> 00:13:13,180
If you're done, beat it!

150
00:13:13,890 --> 00:13:16,520
You lecherous old geezer!

151
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:24,860
Stop!

152
00:13:24,860 --> 00:13:26,860
Stop...!

153
00:13:27,780 --> 00:13:29,780
I'm leaving!

154
00:13:29,780 --> 00:13:33,200
I'm leaving, so just stop!

155
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:46,930
Komurasaki...!

156
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:57,600
Komurasaki the top oiran...

157
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:03,930
is in procession!

158
00:14:03,950 --> 00:14:06,700
Oiran Komurasaki
Wano's Top Courtesan

159
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:10,830
– Lady Komurasaki!
– Lady Komurasaki!

160
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:17,330
She's stunning!

161
00:14:17,330 --> 00:14:19,710
She's gorgeous!

162
00:14:24,460 --> 00:14:26,890
Oh, she's beautiful...!

163
00:14:26,890 --> 00:14:29,470
She's radiant! My eyes!

164
00:14:33,510 --> 00:14:35,390
Komurasaki!

165
00:14:35,390 --> 00:14:38,600
I sold my house, my family,
and everything else!

166
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:43,800
Give me back my money, you thief!

167
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:48,070
Asking for your gift back?

168
00:14:48,750 --> 00:14:51,690
What a pathetic display...

169
00:14:52,370 --> 00:14:57,500
To me, men are just dogs
who fetch me money.

170
00:14:57,500 --> 00:15:00,330
If you can't do that anymore,
you're dead to me.

171
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:07,510
Gentlemen, that's as far as you go!

172
00:15:08,810 --> 00:15:11,510
If your wallets are empty, then get lost!

173
00:15:11,510 --> 00:15:15,720
Anyone who can't generate wealth
has no place in the Flower Capital.

174
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:20,270
In the name of Shogun Orochi,
we'll expel you from the city!

175
00:15:23,390 --> 00:15:25,400
Please don't!

176
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:29,400
The conditions outside the city are inhumane!

177
00:15:29,400 --> 00:15:31,990
Damn! Go to hell!

178
00:15:31,990 --> 00:15:35,130
Komurasaki!

179
00:15:36,100 --> 00:15:40,410
I have nothing but scorn...

180
00:15:40,410 --> 00:15:43,080
for the poor.

181
00:16:00,350 --> 00:16:03,170
Open the gate!

182
00:16:11,120 --> 00:16:15,740
Komurasaki the top oiran has arrived!

183
00:16:33,880 --> 00:16:36,810
So you have a little sister, Momo?

184
00:16:36,810 --> 00:16:38,010
Hey, Tama!

185
00:16:38,010 --> 00:16:41,430
It is rude to address me so casually!
Who do you think I am?!

186
00:16:41,430 --> 00:16:42,940
You're Momo.

187
00:16:43,940 --> 00:16:45,060
Forget it.

188
00:16:46,650 --> 00:16:49,390
Yes, I have a little sister.

189
00:16:49,390 --> 00:16:51,530
If she is alive, she would be twenty-six.

190
00:16:52,410 --> 00:16:57,990
There were witnesses to my mother's death,
but no one has confirmed whether Hiyori died.

191
00:16:57,990 --> 00:17:02,830
So I have faith that she is still out there!

192
00:17:02,830 --> 00:17:05,170
I hope you get to see her again.

193
00:17:05,170 --> 00:17:07,080
Well, I won't!

194
00:17:07,080 --> 00:17:11,510
If her identity were to be exposed,
Orochi would target her!

195
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:15,570
We will reunite only when the battle is won!

196
00:17:15,810 --> 00:17:18,230
Kozuki Momonosuke
Son of Wano's Late Daimyo of Kuri

197
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:26,460
You think you can show up late to work
because of some gorgeous oiran, Franko?!

198
00:17:26,460 --> 00:17:27,940
No, Boss!

199
00:17:27,940 --> 00:17:29,770
I'm so sorry!

200
00:17:30,700 --> 00:17:34,070
I mean, it's hard to believe
such a beauty exists!

201
00:17:35,920 --> 00:17:39,050
I know how you feel!

202
00:17:42,840 --> 00:17:47,500
But you know I have my
reputation to uphold, you dolt!

203
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:50,260
Minatomo
Legendary Master Carpenter
The Man Who Built Kaido's Mansion

204
00:17:50,250 --> 00:17:53,010
Yes! I'm so sorry!

205
00:17:53,010 --> 00:17:59,470
I had no intention of bringing dishonor to the name
of Minatomo, the legendary master carpenter!

206
00:18:00,100 --> 00:18:03,310
Since you put in ten times the amount
of work than anyone else,

207
00:18:03,310 --> 00:18:06,330
I guess I don't mind if you
ditch work sometimes.

208
00:18:06,330 --> 00:18:11,860
If you show me the plans of
the Onigashima stronghold you built,

209
00:18:11,860 --> 00:18:12,900
I'll put in ten–

210
00:18:12,900 --> 00:18:17,070
No! A hundred times the amount of work!

211
00:18:17,990 --> 00:18:19,630
Oh, yeah.

212
00:18:19,630 --> 00:18:26,160
About those Onigashima mansion blueprints
you keep asking me about...

213
00:18:26,160 --> 00:18:29,120
About those... Um...

214
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:36,470
Oh, this is just a tissue.

215
00:18:37,500 --> 00:18:38,630
Oh, come on!

216
00:18:41,090 --> 00:18:42,350
About those...

217
00:18:46,680 --> 00:18:48,440
I just remembered...

218
00:18:50,890 --> 00:18:54,320
I pawned them about ten years ago!

219
00:19:08,590 --> 00:19:14,170
Why the hell do you think I've been
working for you for all these weeks?!

220
00:19:14,170 --> 00:19:17,630
Ouch! Damn it, cut it out, Franko!

221
00:19:21,550 --> 00:19:25,180
You attacked your master!
Who do you think you are?!

222
00:19:25,180 --> 00:19:27,310
You blockhead!

223
00:19:27,310 --> 00:19:29,480
You're driving me crazy!

224
00:19:31,230 --> 00:19:32,270
Eat this!

225
00:19:32,270 --> 00:19:35,480
Franosuke Rocket Launcher!

226
00:19:40,780 --> 00:19:43,870
You're fired! Get out of here, you simpleton!

227
00:19:43,870 --> 00:19:46,490
Gladly! I no longer have
business here anyway!

228
00:19:49,210 --> 00:19:52,790
Blueprints pawned ten years ago?

229
00:19:53,510 --> 00:19:56,670
It's rare that we would ever take those...

230
00:19:58,990 --> 00:20:00,380
Oh, maybe those!

231
00:20:00,380 --> 00:20:02,720
What? Do you have them?!

232
00:20:02,720 --> 00:20:07,070
Well, of course, they've long since
gone to somebody else...

233
00:20:07,070 --> 00:20:09,770
Now, who would've bought such an item...?

234
00:20:09,770 --> 00:20:12,890
Hmm, who was it...?

235
00:20:12,890 --> 00:20:15,610
Um...

236
00:20:16,420 --> 00:20:17,690
Oh, yeah!

237
00:20:18,340 --> 00:20:22,700
It was Kumagoro from the tenements.
He said he'd study them. No doubt about it!

238
00:20:22,700 --> 00:20:24,990
Kumagoro
From the Tenements

239
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,160
Who?!

240
00:20:24,990 --> 00:20:25,030
Kumagoro
From the Tenements

241
00:20:25,030 --> 00:20:25,070
Kumagoro
From the Tenements

242
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:25,200
Who?!

243
00:20:25,200 --> 00:20:25,240
Who?!

244
00:20:25,240 --> 00:20:25,280
Who?!

245
00:20:26,100 --> 00:20:28,790
Kumagoro!

246
00:20:28,790 --> 00:20:30,790
Blueprints?

247
00:20:30,790 --> 00:20:34,100
Oh yeah, I had them at one point,

248
00:20:34,100 --> 00:20:38,550
but I fell behind on my rent,
so my landlord Mr. Kobe took them.

249
00:20:38,550 --> 00:20:41,380
Kobe
The Landlord

250
00:20:39,590 --> 00:20:41,470
Who the hell is that?

251
00:20:41,380 --> 00:20:41,420
Kobe
The Landlord

252
00:20:41,470 --> 00:20:41,510
Who the hell is that?

253
00:20:41,510 --> 00:20:41,550
Who the hell is that?

254
00:20:41,550 --> 00:20:41,590
Who the hell is that?

255
00:20:41,590 --> 00:20:41,630
Who the hell is that?

256
00:20:42,420 --> 00:20:44,130
Kobe!

257
00:20:44,130 --> 00:20:49,990
Oh, the blueprints. They were of high quality,
so I gave them to my favorite geisha.

258
00:20:49,990 --> 00:20:50,970
Miss Kisegawa.

259
00:20:50,970 --> 00:20:52,400
Do you know her?

260
00:20:50,970 --> 00:20:53,350
Kisegawa
A Favored Geisha

261
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:53,480
No!

262
00:20:53,350 --> 00:20:53,390
Kisegawa
