341
00:23:54,870 --> 00:23:57,740
Ebisu Town

342
00:24:00,410 --> 00:24:01,790
Yasu!

343
00:24:02,790 --> 00:24:05,960
Oh, you're back, Tonoyasu!

344
00:24:05,960 --> 00:24:09,590
Yasu, you're back, but we
still don't have any food!

345
00:24:11,080 --> 00:24:12,760
I'm so hungry!

346
00:24:13,690 --> 00:24:15,550
I'm starving to death!

347
00:24:24,800 --> 00:24:27,400
How come they're so cheerful?

348
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:28,860
Wow!

349
00:24:28,860 --> 00:24:33,200
You're quick on the uptake, mister!
Everyone here looks happy, right?!

350
00:24:33,940 --> 00:24:36,660
It's slightly different from
Okobore Town in Kuri.

351
00:24:39,070 --> 00:24:43,790
Amongst all the species,
only humans can laugh!

352
00:24:43,790 --> 00:24:44,670
Yeah!

353
00:24:44,670 --> 00:24:48,900
♪ That's why you just gotta laugh! ♪

354
00:24:50,680 --> 00:24:52,760
♪ You just gotta laugh! ♪

355
00:24:54,970 --> 00:24:57,280
♪ You just gotta laugh! ♪

356
00:25:00,720 --> 00:25:02,680
Pardon us!

357
00:25:11,590 --> 00:25:12,990
– Shogun Orochi!
– Shogun Orochi!

358
00:25:21,200 --> 00:25:25,120
Don't be reserved! Raise your heads!

359
00:25:26,330 --> 00:25:30,090
Now, what's for dinner?

360
00:25:30,090 --> 00:25:33,380
Yes! Everything is ready!

361
00:25:33,380 --> 00:25:34,620
Bring it in!

362
00:25:37,340 --> 00:25:39,220
Oh!

363
00:25:39,220 --> 00:25:43,400
We slaughtered the chickens we bred in
the beautiful environs of Orochi Farm,

364
00:25:43,400 --> 00:25:45,060
then parboiled them...

365
00:25:45,060 --> 00:25:47,060
No! I don't feel like chicken!

366
00:25:47,060 --> 00:25:49,600
Yes, my lord! We'll discard them!

367
00:25:49,600 --> 00:25:51,100
Take it away!

368
00:25:51,100 --> 00:25:52,150
Next!

369
00:25:52,150 --> 00:25:54,450
These fresh, delicious vegetables...

370
00:25:54,450 --> 00:25:55,370
I don't want them!

371
00:25:55,370 --> 00:25:57,280
Yes, my lord! We'll throw them out!

372
00:25:57,280 --> 00:25:58,360
Next!

373
00:25:59,390 --> 00:26:02,450
We present some of the finest,
fattiest saury available!

374
00:26:03,620 --> 00:26:06,100
I like saury!

375
00:26:06,100 --> 00:26:07,900
And tuna sashimi!

376
00:26:07,910 --> 00:26:10,790
Yeah! Nothing beats tuna! Tuna!

377
00:26:10,790 --> 00:26:14,880
And we have selected a variety
of sake from across Wano...

378
00:26:14,880 --> 00:26:16,840
I get it!

379
00:26:18,410 --> 00:26:21,730
Of course you have plenty
of sake to go around!

380
00:26:21,730 --> 00:26:24,120
But how about women?

381
00:26:24,120 --> 00:26:25,770
Of course, right away!

382
00:26:25,770 --> 00:26:27,890
Good! Good!

383
00:26:33,980 --> 00:26:36,920
Mom, I'm hungry!

384
00:26:36,920 --> 00:26:38,780
Me, too!

385
00:26:41,570 --> 00:26:45,450
My tooth fell out from malnutrition!

386
00:26:46,900 --> 00:26:49,280
Not like you have any food to chew anyway!

387
00:26:51,170 --> 00:26:54,960
Now, Tonoyasu, who is this ronin fellow?

388
00:26:54,960 --> 00:26:57,760
He has three swords belted on!

389
00:26:58,760 --> 00:27:01,580
You're right! Three swords!

390
00:27:01,580 --> 00:27:03,260
And they're all long swords!

391
00:27:03,260 --> 00:27:05,100
Are you trying to be funny?!

392
00:27:07,090 --> 00:27:11,790
Whoa, whoa! I admire this gentleman!

393
00:27:11,790 --> 00:27:16,400
Oh no! I'm sorry to hear you've had
this weirdo following you around.

394
00:27:16,400 --> 00:27:19,820
Wrong! I'm the world's greatest sycophant!

395
00:27:19,820 --> 00:27:22,020
Right, handsome?!

396
00:27:23,000 --> 00:27:27,500
He sure is, but look!
He has that frightful expression!

397
00:27:27,500 --> 00:27:31,830
Come on, young man. Drop the scary look.

398
00:27:34,300 --> 00:27:36,710
Give us a smile!

399
00:27:36,710 --> 00:27:40,300
Good things happen, even in
a miserable hole like Ebisu!

400
00:27:40,300 --> 00:27:44,970
Wait, are you saying he
paid this town a visit?!

401
00:27:44,970 --> 00:27:49,930
That's right! The Witching Hour Boy
paid us another visit!

402
00:27:51,520 --> 00:27:53,310
That's great!

403
00:27:53,310 --> 00:27:55,480
Witching-whozit?

404
00:27:55,480 --> 00:27:59,400
Yeah, he always comes by
when we're in trouble!

405
00:27:59,400 --> 00:28:02,830
We don't even know who he is.

406
00:28:04,120 --> 00:28:07,900
He appears at the witching hour

407
00:28:07,900 --> 00:28:11,460
and steals money from the rich,
evil people of the capital...

408
00:28:19,400 --> 00:28:23,690
He leaves the money at
poor tenements and disappears.

409
00:28:23,690 --> 00:28:26,630
I wonder who he is.

410
00:28:26,630 --> 00:28:29,510
Thank goodness, thank goodness!

411
00:28:30,600 --> 00:28:32,940
Fortune comes to those who laugh!

412
00:28:32,940 --> 00:28:37,160
So we pooled our money to ourselves a treat!

413
00:28:38,320 --> 00:28:41,150
Oh! What kind of treat?!

414
00:28:41,150 --> 00:28:43,130
Here it is!

415
00:28:43,130 --> 00:28:44,410
You see?

416
00:28:44,410 --> 00:28:46,280
This is it!

417
00:28:47,190 --> 00:28:49,120
Please have a cup!

418
00:28:50,850 --> 00:28:52,460
You should have some, too!

419
00:28:54,190 --> 00:28:56,000
It's clear water!

420
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:58,340
We bought it with the money we were given!

421
00:29:01,840 --> 00:29:04,050
No, I shouldn't...

422
00:29:04,050 --> 00:29:05,730
Don't worry!

423
00:29:06,890 --> 00:29:11,390
This water's clean, so you
won't get a tummy ache!

424
00:29:11,390 --> 00:29:16,090
Yasu brought you here,
so you must be a good man!

425
00:29:20,520 --> 00:29:22,800
Don't be shy!

426
00:29:22,800 --> 00:29:27,620
Go ahead and drink! Everyone
has the right to have some!

